<subSubSection id="C31719EEFFEFC94A72B0E23EFA0AFB7D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="key">
<keyStep id="30F952C0FFEFC94A72B0E23EFA0BFC9B" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E23EFA0BFCF7" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" box="[136,1451,804,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E23EFA0BFCF7" box="[136,1451,804,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1. Free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 4(–7) strongly elongate rectangular cells ........................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E25AFA0BFC9B" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" box="[136,1451,833,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E25AFA0BFC9B" box="[136,1451,833,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1. Free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 7–18 subquadrate to shortly rectangular cells.................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F952C0FFEFC94A72B0E245FA0AFC07" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E245FA0BFC5C" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E245FA0BFC5C" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
2. Leaf lobe acute at apex; free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 4(–7) cells. Male bracteoles present throughout the androecial shoot. Leaf lobe with 1 or 2 ocelli ......................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D31E6FFEFC94A771BE267FA0BFC5C" authorityName="Grolle &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2000" box="[1315,1451,892,913]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Drepanolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="commutata">
<emphasis id="B9799677FFEFC94A771BE267FA0BFC5C" box="[1315,1451,892,913]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">D. commutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E283FA0AFC07" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E283FA0AFC07" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
2. Leaf lobe rounded at apex; free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 4 cells. Male bracteoles restricted at the basal portion of the androecial shoot. Leaf lobe with two monoliate ocelli........................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D31E6FFEFC94A7770E2AEFA0AFC07" authorityName="Grolle &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Stephani" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1352,1450,949,970]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Drepanolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis id="B9799677FFEFC94A7770E2AEFA0AFC07" box="[1352,1450,949,970]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">D. spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F952C0FFEFC94A72B0E2CAFA0BFBF0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E2CAFA0AFBC9" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E2CAFA0AFBC9" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
3. Free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 12−18 cells. Underleaf lobes triangular, consisting of 12 cells long, 3−4 cells wide at base. Leaf lobe with a single ocellus................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D31E6FFEFC94A7708E2F4FA0AFBC9" authorityName="Grolle &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Bischler" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[1328,1450,1007,1028]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Drepanolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis id="B9799677FFEFC94A7708E2F4FA0AFBC9" box="[1328,1450,1007,1028]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">D. siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E510FA0BFBF0" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E510FA0BFBF0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">3. Free lateral lobular margin proximal to the notch bordered by 7–12 cells. Underleaf lobes needle-like or linear-triangular, consisting of 6−12 cells long, 2−3 cells wide at base. Leaf lobe with 1 or 2 ocelli ............................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F952C0FFEFC94A72B0E55EFA0AFB7D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E55EFA0BFBBA" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E55EFA0BFBBA" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
4. Male bracteoles present throughout the androecial shoot. Underleaf lobes consisting of 6−8 cells long. Leaf lobe with (1−)2 ocelli ............................................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D31E6FFEFC94A772FE579FA0BFBBA" authorityName="Grolle &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="P. C. Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[1303,1451,1122,1143]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Drepanolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="B9799677FFEFC94A772FE579FA0BFBBA" box="[1303,1451,1122,1143]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">D. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB24A65FFEFC94A72B0E565FA0AFB7D" blockId="1.[136,1452,772,1201]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30FCE950FFEFC94A72B0E565FA0AFB7D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
4. Male bracteoles restricted at the basal portion of the androecial shoot. Underleaf lobes consisting of 8−12 cells long. Leaf lobe with 1−2 ocelli .......................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D31E6FFEFC94A770CE587FA0AFB7D" authorityName="Stephani" authorityYear="1913" box="[1332,1450,1179,1201]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Drepanolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="fleischeri">
<emphasis id="B9799677FFEFC94A770CE587FA0AFB7D" box="[1332,1450,1179,1201]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">D. fleischeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
